    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-15T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-15T16:00:00-05:00" n="860"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d860">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/8346: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-15T15:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 15, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>126. President Sacasa, in his address at the opening of Congress today,
                    emphatically declined to remain in office after the expiration of his present
                    constitutional term. He expressed hope to be able to present to the Congress for
                    consideration during present session, trade agreement with the United
                        States.<note n="94" xml:id="d860fn94">See <ref target="#pg_814">pp.
                            814</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <p>At elections held yesterday for officers of the Congress, supporters of Sacasa
                    were triumphant. This may be interpreted as indication that present Congress is
                    opposed to amendment of constitution to permit Somoza to succeed to the
                    Presidency.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
